  "prompt": "Do all or most of the North Indians drink alcohol?",
  "response": "North India, like other regions of India, is diverse and people's habits and lifestyles vary greatly. While alcohol consumption exists, it is not universally prevalent among all North Indians. Drinking habits can be influenced by various factors including cultural norms, religious beliefs, personal preferences, and social practices. \n\nFor example, some people abstain due to religious reasons, particularly among communities such as Hindus, Muslims, Sikhs, and others who might have specific religious teachings about alcohol. Others might choose not to drink for health reasons or personal choices. On the other hand, there are people who do drink alcohol socially or occasionally.\n\nIt is essential to understand that generalizing about the behavior of a large and diverse population can lead to inaccuracies. Individual choices about alcohol consumption can vary widely.",
